We first compute the Gross Profit Margin by dividing Gross Profit by Total Revenue.

• Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue  
  = 2610115.02 / 5695115.02  
  ≈ 0.4583, or 45.83%

Next, we calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio. In this task (and following the sample’s approach) we use the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities divided by Total Current Liabilities.

• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
  = (-224133.22) / 829755.77  
  ≈ -0.2702, or rounded to -0.27

Thus, the answers in the specified format are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "45.83%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-0.27"
  }
}
